data.text: clothes ♦ clothing ♦ garment ♦ dress ♦ wear ♦ gear

data.chText: 以上各词均指衣服、服装。
data.enText: These are all words for the things that you wear, such as shirts, jackets, dresses and trousers.
the things that you wear, such as shirts, jackets, dresses and trousers

data.chText: 指衣服，尤指某种类型的服装：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) clothes, especially a particular type of clothes

data.chText: clothing较clothes更正式，尤用以指某种类型的服装。clothes或clothing无单数形式，指一件衣服用a piece/an item/an article of clothing。
data.enText: Clothing is more formal than clothes and is used especially to mean ‘a particular type of clothes’. There is no singular form of clothes or clothing : a piece/an item/an article of clothing is used to talk about one thing that you wear such as a dress or shirt.

data.chText: 他穿着一件没样子的奇怪衣服。
data.enText: He was wearing a strange shapeless garment.

data.chText: garment只用于正式场合或文学语境，在日常生活中，一件衣服用a piece of clothing。
data.enText: Garment should only be used in formal or literary contexts; in everyday contexts use a piece of clothing .

data.chText: 指着装、衣着，尤指某种样式或某种场合穿的衣服：
data.enText: clothes, especially when worn in a particular style or for a particular occasion

data.chText: 我们在星期五可以穿便服。
data.enText: We were allowed to wear casual dress on Fridays.

data.chText: （通常构成复合词）指某种用途或场合穿的衣服，尤指于商店售卖的衣服：
data.enText: (usually in compounds) clothes for a particular purpose or occasion, especially when it is being sold in shops/stores

data.chText: 她的朋友都穿着最新款的衣服。
data.enText: Her friends were all wearing the latest gear (= fashionable clothes) .

data.chText: 以上各词均指特定目的或活动所需的材料、设备、器材。
data.enText: These are all words for the things that you need for a particular purpose or activity.

data.chText: 指特定目的或活动所需的设备、器材：
data.enText: the things that are needed for a particular purpose or activity

data.enText: Equipment is usually solid things, especially large ones. Materials may be liquids, powders or books, CDs, etc. containing information, as well as small solid items.

trans: 为…做准备；为做…做好了准备

tr: a toothed wheel that engages another toothed mechanism in order to change the speed or direction of transmitted motion
equipment consisting of miscellaneous articles needed for a particular operation or sport etc.
a mechanism for transmitting motion for some specific purpose (as the steering gear of a vehicle)
wheelwork consisting of a connected set of rotating gears by which force is transmitted or motion or torque is changed
example: the fool got his tie caught in the geartrain

tr: set the level or character of
example: She pitched her speech to the teenagers in the audience

value.def: The gears on a machine or vehicle are a device for changing the rate at which energy is changed into motion.

example.ex: On hills, he must use low gears...
example.tran: 在山上,他必须挂低速挡。

example.ex: The car was in fourth gear...
He put the truck in gear and drove on.
example.tran: 他把卡车挂上挡，继续往前开。

value.def: The gear involved in a particular activity is the equipment or special clothing that you use.

example.ex: About 100 officers in riot gear were needed to break up the fight.
example.tran: 大约需要100名穿防暴服的警察前来制止这场斗殴。

example.ex: They helped us put our gear back into the van.
example.tran: 他们帮我们把装备放回到小货车里。

example.ex: I used to wear trendy gear but it just looked ridiculous.
example.tran: 我以前常穿新潮的衣服，但看上去却滑稽可笑。

value.def: Some people refer to illegal drugs, especially heroin, as gear .

example.ex: Are these people using gear and amphetamines at the same time?
example.tran: 这些人同时服用海洛因和安非他明吗？

value.def: If someone or something is geared to or towards a particular purpose, they are organized or designed in order to achieve that purpose.

example.ex: Colleges are not always geared to the needs of mature students...
example.tran: 大学有时满足不了成人学生的需求。

example.ex: My training was geared towards winning gold in Munich.
example.tran: 我为了在慕尼黑夺取金牌而进行训练。

value.tran: 使为…而准备；使为了达到…而作好准备
